<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head>
		<title>CSS Test: flowing content with opacity &lt; 1 in region</title>
		<link href="mailto:mibalan@adobe.com" rel="author" title="Mihai Balan" />
		<link href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-regions/#the-flow-into-property" rel="help" />
		<link href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-regions/#flow-from" rel="help" />
		<meta content="ahem" name="flags" />
		<meta content="Test checks that content with opacity &lt; 1 is correctly flowed into regions. This might fail on implementations that use layers for compositing but don't properly handle content flowing." name="assert" />
		<link href="reference/content-node-layers-001-ref.xht" rel="match" />
		<style>
		#content {
			font-family: Ahem;
			font-size: 20px;
			line-height: 1em;
			color: #5555FF;
				/*a light-ish blue, to give us a nice purple when alpha-blended with red*/
			opacity: 0.5;
			flow-into: f;
		}
		#region {
			width: 100px;
			height: 100px;
			background-color: red;
			flow-from: f;
		}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<ol>
			<li>You should see no red.</li>
			<li>Test passes if you see a purple square below.</li>
		</ol>
		<div id="content">xxxxx<br />xxxxx<br />xxxxx<br />xxxxx<br />xxxxx</div>
		<div id="region"></div>
	
</body></html>